<br>
Kael quest givers are Kromzek (storm) but they sit behind a couple of Tormax faction guys (and Tormax himself if hes up). Easiest way if you're better than indiff with Kromzek (need kindly, warmly or ally to complete the quests I think) is to get a CoH mage to drop you right next to the quest givers.<br>
<br>
If you're KoS to Kromzek kill in SS for a while, faction goes up pretty quick there. Once you're dubious to Kromzek, purchase a whack load of dorf heads, invis to the bank and hand the heads to Captain Bvellious. Funny thing about the heads is the give Kromrif, Kromzek, Tormax faction and drop Yelinak but not dorf. If you havn't keeled many giants then you'll go non-KoS to all 3 factions reasonably quickly. Everyone in and around the bank is Kromzek so you shouldn't have too much trouble, just be aware though, theres 1 Kromrif wanderer that comes within agro range of the bank.<br>
<br>
I was as bad as I could get with all 3 faction (i.e. 'your faction with ...... could not possibly get any worse'), with keeling in ToV though my faction sky rocketed. Now Ally with Kromzek but still KoS to Kromrif and Tormax, but being a monk I havn't worried about the other factions too much as I've been able to sneak/feign past Tormax and his guards to get my quest armors. I also started handing heads to Bvellious and funnily enough I'm still ally to the dorfs, hehe. <p>Kracs Knuckles<BR>
